com.cyc.kb.client

Class AssertionImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.kb.client.KbObjectImpl
      • com.cyc.kb.client.AssertionImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.cyc.kb.Assertion, com.cyc.kb.KbObject
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FactImpl, RuleImpl

    public class AssertionImpl
extends KbObjectImpl
implements com.cyc.kb.Assertion
    An Assertion object is a facade for a #$CycLAssertion in Cyc KB. An assertion is a semantically well formed Sentence, in a specific Context.

    Sub-classes include Fact and Rule.

    Since:
    1.0

      • get

        public static com.cyc.kb.Assertion get(String hlid)
                                throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException,
                                       com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        Get the Assertion object that corresponds to hlid. Throws exceptions if the hlid isn't in the KB, or if it's not already an assertion. NOTE: The get (String ) factory methods in other classes find objects based on hlid or string representation of the object. They use nameOrId as the string variable name. But this method finds objects based on hlid alone. This is because it is much more common and easier to find assertions based on two strings, formula and context.
        Parameters:
        hlid - the hlid corresponding to the assertion in the KB
        Returns:
        an Assertion based on hlid
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException - if assertion based on hlid is not an instance of assertion
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException

                                throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException,
                                       com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        Get the Assertion object that corresponds to formulaStr in the context corresponding to ctxStr. Throws exceptions if no such formula is found in the specified context in the KB, or if it's not already an assertion.
        Parameters:

        ctxStr - string representation of the context of the formula
        Returns:

        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbObjectNotFoundException - if no Assertion with the given formula string is found in the context

      • findOrCreate

        public static com.cyc.kb.Assertion findOrCreate(String formulaStr)
                                         throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException,
                                                com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        Finds or creates the Assertion object that corresponds to formulaStr in the default assertion context. Tries to assert if no such formula is found in the specified context in the KB. Throws an exception if it is unable to make such an assertion. Strength is set to Strength.DEFAULT by default Direction is set to Direction.FORWARD by default
        Parameters:
        formulaStr - the string representation of the formula to be found or created
        Returns:
        an Assertion based on formulaStr and the default assertion context
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.InvalidFormulaInContextException - if no assertion with the given formula string is found or created in the context

      • findOrCreate

        public static com.cyc.kb.Assertion findOrCreate(com.cyc.kb.Sentence formula,
                                com.cyc.kb.Context ctx)
                                         throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException,
                                                com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        Finds or creates the Assertion object that corresponds to formula in ctx. Tries to assert if no such formula is found in the specified context in the KB. Throws an exception if it is unable to make such an assertion. NOTE: All findOrCreate factory methods that take CycObject do not eventually create any new object in the assertion because (most of) the CycObjects can only be built based on objects in the KB. Some exceptions are Sentences, Variables and Symbols. NAUTs are also not in the KB, but in the API they are effectively treated as being in the KB. Strength is set to Strength.DEFAULT by default Direction is set to Direction.FORWARD by default
        Parameters:
        formula - the formula to be found or created
        ctx - the context of the formula
        Returns:
        an Assertion based on formula and context
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.InvalidFormulaInContextException - if no assertion with the given formula string is found or created in the context

      • findOrCreate

        public static com.cyc.kb.Assertion findOrCreate(com.cyc.kb.Sentence formula)
                                         throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException,
                                                com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        Find or creates the Assertion object that corresponds to formula in the default assertion context (@link KBAPIConfiguration}. Tries to assert if no such formula is found in the KB. Throws an exception if it is unable to make such an assertion. NOTE: All findOrCreate factory methods that take CycObject do not eventually create any new object in the assertion because (most of) the CycObjects can only be built based on objects in the KB. Some exceptions are Sentences, Variables and Symbols. NAUTs are also not in the KB, but in the API they are effectively treated as being in the KB. Strength is set to Strength.DEFAULT by default Direction is set to Direction.FORWARD by default
        Parameters:
        formula - the formula to be found or created
        Returns:
        an Assertion based on the formula in the default assertion context
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
